<HEAD>List of New Czechoslovak Cabinet Members</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Czechoslovakia, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PRAGUE, Czechoslovakia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a list of the new,
21-member government sworn in Sunday in Czechoslovakia.
   Premier: Marian Calfa. Communist Party.
   First Vice Premier: Valtr Komarek. Communist Party. Proposed by
the opposition.
   First Vice Premier: former dissident Jan Carnogursky. Proposed
by the opposition. Unaffiliated.
   Vice Premier: Frantisek Pitra. Communist Party. Also Communist
head of the Czech regional government.
   Vice Premier for Scientific and Technological Development:
Frantisek Reichel. People's Party. Supported by the opposition.
   Vice Premier for State Planning Commission: Vladimir Dlouhy.
Communist Party. Supported by the opposition.
   Vice Premier: Josef Hromadka. Unaffiliated.
   Vice Premier for Agriculture: Oldrich Bursky. Socialist Party.
   Foreign Minister: former dissident Jiri Dienstbier. Proposed by
the opposition. Unaffiliated.
   Defense Minister: Miroslav Vacek. Communist Party.
   Finance Minister: Vaclav Klaus. Proposed by the opposition.
Unaffiliated.
   Labor and Social Affairs Minister: former dissident Petr Miller.
Proposed by the opposition. Unaffiliated.
   Foreign Trade Minister: Andrej Barcak. Communist Party.
   Transportation and Communications Minister: Frantisek Podlena.
Communist Party.
   Engineering Minister: Ladislav Vodrazka. Communist Party.
   Energy Minister: Frantisek Pinc. Communist Party.
   Minister of People's Control (Treasury): Kvetoslava Korinkova.
Unaffiliated.
   Minister of Price Controls: Ladislav Dvorak. Socialist Party.
   Minister without portfolio: Robert Martinko. Unaffiliated.
   Minister without portfolio: Richard Sacher. People's Party.
Supported by the opposition.
   The Communist head of the Slovak regional government, one of two
regional bodies in Czechoslovakia, will be named as an additional
vice premier. The new regional government is to be named Dec. 13.
   The Interior Ministry, which runs the nation's secret and
uniformed police, will be run by Calfa, Komarek and Carnogursky.
</TEXT>
