<FIRST>r a PM-Quayle-Zionism     12-11 0208</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Quayle-Zionism,0217</SECOND>
<HEAD>Calls on Soviets to Help Repeal UN `Racism' Resolution</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Vice President Dan Quayle wants the Soviet Union
to work to repeal a 1975 United Nations resolution that equated
Zionism with racism.
   Quayle also said he planned to tell U.N. Secretary-General
Javier Perez de Cuellar today that the United States wants the
resolution repealed.
   He said he planned to present Perez de Cuellar with a $65
million check for U.S. obligations to the world body.
   On Sunday, Quayle said Soviet President Mikhail Gorbachev should
show that he wants the United Nations to play a bigger role in
world affairs by helping sponsor a new resolution.
   ``This resolution would state that Zionism is not and never had
been a form of racism. Furthermore, we would declare once and for
all the Zionism-is-racism resolution null and void,'' Quayle told a
Yeshiva University audience at the Waldorf-Astoria Hotel, where he
received an honorary Doctor of Laws degree.
   Quayle praised the Soviet Union's ``new thinking'' in moving
away from its anti-Israel propaganda.
   But the Soviet Union, which was instrumental in passing the 1975
resolution, can do more by helping ``gain repeal of this loathsome
provision,'' Quayle said.
   Zionism is the ideology on which Israel is based.
</TEXT>
