<SECOND>PM-Houston Police Shootings, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0487,0307</SECOND>
<HEAD>Second Officer Killed in Two Days</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Leads with 4 grafs to UPDATE with victim's name, suspect in
custody and CORRECT officer was a 17-year veteran, sted 15-year. Picks
up 5th graf pvs, `On Saturday...'.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An off-duty police officer and a 26-year-old
woman were shot to death in the second slaying of a Houston police
officer in two days, authorities said.
   Officer John Mendell, 43, and Mary Heather Ballard were killed
Sunday night at the woman's apartment, officials said. Mendell was
a 17-year veteran of the force.
   Police believe the shooting resulted from a domestic dispute
involving a man who was the officer's roommate. The man had once
dated Ms. Ballard, police said.
   Shortly after the shootings, the roommate turned himself in to
police in Bellarie, a Houston suburb, in connection with the
slayings, said police Sgt. David Preece. His name was not
immediately released.
   On Saturday, Officer James Charles Boswell, 29, was shot by a
man who approached him in his car.
   Craig Neal Ogan, 35, who is charged with capital murder in the
shooting, was a federal drug informant in St. Louis but wasn't
involved in any narcotics investigation in Houston, said John Bott,
a Drug Enforcement Administration spokesman here.
   ``I do know for a fact that he was working for us up there. As
far as what he was doing up there, I don't know,'' Bott said.
   Police said Ogan, who previously lived in Houston, had checked
into a motel and complained about the heat and telephone service.
He threatened the clerk before walking across the street to
Boswell's patrol car, where he shot the officer, police said.
   Ogan was shot by Boswell's partner. He was in fair condition
today at Ben Taub and under guard by sheriff's deputies.
</TEXT>
