<HEAD>45 Killed in Bus-Truck Collision in Lampung</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An overcrowded bus and a truck
collided head-on in Lampung, South Sumatra, killing 45 people and
injuring 20 others, a newspaper reported Monday.
   A stalled car on the road apparently prevented the two drivers
from seeing each other as they approached from opposite directions
Saturday in the town of Tanjungan, about 115 miles northwest of
Jakarta, the newspaper Pelita said.
   The bus, carrying 60 people, was en route from Bakahuni, a ferry
port on Sumatra's southeastern coast, to Rajabasa, in the same
province, Pelita said.
