   The annual Christmas open house at the governor's mansion will
be held Wednesday afternoon and about 1,700 Juneau residents are
expected to attend.
   The event has been held annually since the three-story colonial
mansion was built in 1912, except for two years during World War
II. Visitors will be greeted by Cowper, his wife, Michael, Lt. Gov.
Stephen McAlpine and his wife, Dana.
