<FILEID>AP-NR-12-11-89 1759EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r w BC-Bush-Text 5thADD   12-11 0806</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Bush-Text, 5th ADD,800</SECOND>
<HEAD>WASHINGTON: ... really. Yes?</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Q: Mr. President ... In your inaugural address, you called for a
higher level of cooperation between the Executive and Legislative
branches. And I was wondering, in the past year _ I realize the
House leadership had some unexpected turmoil _ but have you been
pleased, distressed, surprised by the character of White
House-Capitol Hill relations?
   A: Well, being somewhat of a realist, I can't say I was
surprised, but _ and there have been some negative, highly partisan
comments. I pride myself on the fact that I don't believe anybody
can point to a personal observation on the negative side by me
about any of the Democratic leaders, and I'm going to continue that
way. And I try to debrief them when we come back from Malta; I try
to give them a preview and ask for their advice before I go to
Malta; we talk about these domestic issues in a very open way with
the leaders _ and I'm going to continue that.
   And I think in some ways, that's been good _ I've taken some
flack on board from some in our own party for doing that too much,
for trying to work with the Democrats. But I was elected to make
certain things happen, and I'm going to continue to try to make
certain things happen. I cited an unfulfilled agenda here. But I _
if I had to sum up my feelings at the end of the year, I'd say
there are some frustrations, but I'm determined, when the Congress
comes back, to hold out the hand and try again. We have good
relationships with the Speaker, and the Senate side, reasonably
good. And so, we're going _ we're going to keep working on that.
But it _ there've been some good moments and there've been some
enormous frustrations, I guess is the way to wrap it up. Yes, sir?
   Q: Mr. President ... How likely is it for Jennifer Casolo to
receive a fair trial in El Salvador, given the breakdown of law and
order in that country, and also given the initial remarks that came
out of the White House when she was arrested?
   A: Well, I think it's essential that she receive a fair trial.
And I have instructed our ambassador, and indeed talked to
Cristiani personally, to represent to the Salvadorans that it's
essential that a fair trial be granted. And having said that, I am
satisfied so far that that will take place. But it is essential
that it not only take place but that it have all the appearances of
fairness, and I think that's what Mr. Cristiani is determined to
do. So I don't _ that one is _ is _ is very complex, but so far
I've seen no indication that she will not receive a fair trial.
   I have expressed my own concern about the FMLN shooting up
civilians and shooting up _ going after a democratically-elected
government that was elected in certifiably free elections. And I
think when Oscar Arias calls and urges that the Soviets intervene
to see that this kind of thing doesn't go on, it makes an
impression on me. But we ought to separate these cases, and just do
everything we can to insist that, whoever it is, be granted a fair
_ fair hearing and a fair trial. And I hope that will be the case
in Jennifer Casolo. Yes, sir?
   Q: ... Cincinnati being the home of Marvin Warner and Charles
Keating, we've got quite an interest in the S&amp;L crisis. You
mentioned in your remarks that you saw the fact that the S&amp;L
package guaranteed depositors their money as being a positive.
However, some are suggesting that the fact that that maximum level
of insurance is so high it's part of the problem, and I was just
wondering what your thoughts were on that.
   A: On deposit insurance?
   Q: The maximium level of insurance, $100,000 on depositors
insurance, being part of the reason for some of the problems with
Lincoln Savings and so forth.
   A: I _ I just _ I don't want to dodge your question, but I don't
know enough about the specifics in that case to give you an opinion
as to whether the $100,000 limit on savings deposits affected it or
not. All I do know is we've got to clean it up and it's a whale of
a _ a whale of a mess, and we'll see where we go. But we had this
one refinancing. I am now told that that might not be enough. And
whether you can attribute it to your question or now, I am
embarrassed to say I just don't have a good answer for you. Yes,
sir, way in the back.
