from this meeting to another marvelous meeting with Dick Darman _
(laughter) _ and big, thick notebooks over there, so I am not
ducking it, I just don't know the answer. But generally speaking, I
think you're going to find that we are able to finance the
initiatives that I talked about _ some of which I mentioned here _
that do affect the human _ the welfare of the American people,
particularly those that are disadvantaged. Yeah? ... Last two. One,
two.
   Q: ... Mr. President. Could you tell us when a decision will be
announced on the relocation of the Southern Command in Panama?
   A: No, sir, I don't know _ I'm not ducking it, I just don't know
the answer. (Aside) Does anyone _ can anyone help with that? Bob?
   Staff: No, sir.
   A: Can't _ I know people in San Antonio have a keen interest in
this _
   Q: Yes, very keen.
   A: _ and I can understand why, but I just don't know the answer
to that one. Yes, last one.
   Q: ... There have been widely divergent accounts this morning of
the credibility of a witness to the murder of those priests in El
Salvador. Is it not time to go public with that investigation? And
if not now, when?
   A: A widening _ a widely _
   Q: We have a report _
   A: _ as to whether she's a credible witness or not?
   Q: Yes, we have a report out of El Salvador that she had flunked
