   Stock prices declined in lackluster trading
today, erasing most of Friday's gains.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was off 8.32 points to
2,723.12 at 11 a.m. EST. An hour earlier the blue-chip indicator
was down 0.42 point after gaining 10.66 points on Friday.
   Declining issues outnumbered advancers by about 7 to 5 on the
New York Stock Exchange, with 712 issues down, 506 up and 520
unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 46.81 million shares.
   Analysts said weakness in high-technology stocks was helping
push the market lower.
   Profit-taking following Friday's rally also helped depress stock
prices, said Brad Weeks, head of equity trading for Donaldson,
Lufkin &amp; Jenrette.
   Weeks said stock prices could decline further before the market
begins a year-end uptick.
   ``We will probably get more profit-taking today and tomorrow
before we go into some sort of rally,'' Weeks said.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks was
down 0.42 to 192.50.
   At the American Stock Exchange, the market value index was up
0.13 to 375.32.
   Among actively traded issues on the NYSE, Compaq Computer was
down 3~ to 82, Pfizer was off 1{ to 67|, Eastman Kodak was down 1
to 41} and IBM had dropped } to 96[.
   Varity, meanwhile, was up [ to 2{, Toys R Us had gained [ to 35~
and Pinacle West was unchanged at 11.
