<FIRST>r f BC-Ford-Jaguar     12-11 0141</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Ford-Jaguar,0148</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ford Gets Controlling Interest in Jaguar</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DEARBORN, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ford Motor Co. has acquired a controlling
interest in Jaguar PLC as part of its $2.5-billion takeover of the
British luxury-car maker, the No. 2 U.S. automaker said Monday.
   Ford said that by the close of business Friday, it had acquired
77.4 percent of the outstanding shares of Jaguar stock, including
the 13 percent it owned prior to Nov. 2.
   On that day, Ford and Jaguar announced Ford would bid for all of
Jaguar's outstanding stock.
   Analysts have said adding the Jaguar cars to Ford's product line
would enhance Ford's image and provide a more stable financial base
for Jaguar.
   However, they wondered if the price Ford was paying was too
high, considering the likelihood that Ford would have to sink
another $1 billion to upgrade manufacturing processes.
</TEXT>
