<HEAD>Ford Recalls 32,000 1986 Cars Sold in California</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DEARBORN, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ford Motor Co. on Monday recalled 32,000
1986-model cars sold in California because of possible excessive
pollution emissions.
   The company said affected cars include the Ford Mustang,
Thunderbird, LTD and the Mercury Capri, Cougar and Marquis. Each is
equipped with a 3.8-liter, V-6 engine.
   The California Air Resources Board said tests showed the cars
may emit higher-than-permitted amounts of hydrocarbon, according to
Ford.
   Owners will be notified by mail and work on the cars will be
performed free of charge, the company said.
</TEXT>
