<HEAD>Sell Two Divisions</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   National Intergroup Inc. said Monday it has
sold two divisions of its National Aluminum Corp. subsidiary for
about $132.5 million in cash.
   The rolling division was purchased by Norandal USA Inc., a
subsidiary of Noranda Inc. of Toronto, Ontario. The extrusion
division was sold to R.D. Werner Co. Inc. of Greenville, Pa.
   The sale of the two divisions is expected to result in a gain of
about $22 million.
   National Intergroup, based in Pittsburgh, said the sale is part
of its strategy to divest its metal businesses and to focus on
wholesale distribution.
