<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-HomeShopping     12-11 0203</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Home Shopping,0210</SECOND>
<HEAD>Home Shopping Network Announces Record Sales, Income</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Home Shopping Network Inc. on Monday
announced record sales and earnings for the quarter ended Nov. 30,
including an 85 percent increase in profit.
   The results represent a turnaround for the electronic retailer,
which sells products through a television show shown on cable TV
networks. HSN lost $26.1 million in the quarter ended Aug. 31, and
lost $14.9 million for the fiscal year that ended that date.
   For the most recent quarter, net income grew to $20.2 million,
or 21 cents per share, from the $10.9 million, or 12 cents a share,
for the same period last year, the company said.
   Sales for the quarter were a record $255.2 million. That was up
27.2 percent from the $200.6 million reported for the same period
last year, the company said.
   ``The solid gains HSN has reported in the first quarter
reinforce our decision to focus the company's resources to its core
business, electronic retailing,'' said Roy M. Speer, chairman and
chief executive officer.
   The retailing firm has streamlined its operations, Speer said,
and has ``significantly curtailed or eliminated activities that did
not provide adequate returns on our investments.''
