<HEAD>Paramount Acquires TVX Stock</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VIRGINIA BEACH, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   TVX Broadcast Group Inc. said Monday
that Paramount Communications Inc. has acquired preferred and
common stock of the Virginia Beach-based independent television
station owner for $110 million.
   In addition, the New York-based entertainment and publishing
conglomerate acquired about $30 million worth of TVX debt
obligations.
   TVX said the shares acquired by Paramount consist primarily of
convertible preferred stock that when converted to common shares
would give Paramount about a 79 percent stake in TVX. The
conversion requires approval by the Federal Communications
Commission.
   Paramount acquired the shares and debt from TVX's investment
banker, Salomon Brothers Inc., and the acquisition formally ended
Salomon's involvement with TVX.
   ``We exchanged a financial institution for an entertainment
company,'' said Aubrey E. Loving Jr., TVX's chairman. ``We now have
like interests as we go forward with the future.''
   Revenues have improved 11 percent for the first three quarters
of 1989 at five of TVX's eight stations _ in Philadelphia,
Washington, Dallas, Houston and Raleigh, N.C. TVX also holds
stations in San Antonio, Texas, and New Orleans. It plans to sell
the New Orleans station in early 1990.
